2026-03-18 15:03:56.651 +00:00 [INF] API | POST /api/ai | 200 | 5813ms | Headers: {"Content-Type":"application/json; charset=utf-8"} | Body: {"success":true,"data":{"answers":[{"model":"gpt-4o-mini","text":"### Ingredients\n- 2 chicken breasts\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 fillet of fish (such as tilapia or cod)\n- Optional: olive oil, salt, pepper, herbs (like thyme or parsley)\n\n### Instructions\n1. **Prep Chicken**: Lightly season the chicken breasts with salt, pepper, and optional herbs if desired.\n2. **Sear Chicken**: In a skillet over medium heat, add a drizzle of olive oil (optional) and sear the chicken breasts for about 5-6 minutes on each side until golden brown. Remove and set aside.\n3. **Sauté Garlic**: In the same skillet, add the minced garlic and sauté for about 1 minute until fragrant.\n4. **Add Fish**: Place the fish fillet in the skillet with the garlic, cooking for about 3-4 minutes on each side until fully cooked and flaky.\n5. **Combine**: Return the chicken to the skillet with the fish and garlic. Cook everything together for an additional 2-3 minutes, allowing the flavors to meld.\n6. **Serve**: Plate the chicken and fish together, spooning any garlic from the skillet over the top.\n7. **Garnish (Optional)**: Sprinkle with fresh herbs for extra flavor if desired.\n8. **Enjoy**: Serve warm and enjoy your flavorful chicken and fish dish!"}]},"meta":{"provider":"openai","tokensUsed":360,"ingredientsCount":3,"fallbackUsed":false,"originalProvider":"","timestamp":"2026-03-18T15:03:56.6362683Z"},"error":null}
