2026-03-18 15:08:19.466 +00:00 [INF] API | POST /api/ai | 200 | 9043ms | Headers: {"Content-Type":"application/json; charset=utf-8"} | Body: {"success":true,"data":{"answers":[{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","text":"# Garlic Chicken & Fish Skillet\n\nA simple, flavorful one-pan dish where garlic ties both proteins together beautifully.\n\n### Ingredients\n\n**Main:**\n- 2 chicken thighs (boneless)\n- 2 fish fillets (white fish like tilapia or cod works great)\n- 6 cloves garlic, minced\n\n**Optional:**\n- Olive oil\n- Salt & pepper\n- Fresh parsley\n- Lemon juice\n- Butter\n\n---\n\n### Instructions\n\n1. **Season** both the chicken and fish generously with salt, pepper, and half the minced garlic.\n2. Heat a skillet over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil *(or cook dry if preferred)*.\n3. **Sear the chicken** for 5–6 minutes per side until golden and cooked through. Remove and set aside.\n4. Lower heat to medium and **add the remaining garlic** to the pan, stirring for 30 seconds until fragrant.\n5. **Add the fish fillets** to the same pan, cooking 3–4 minutes per side, basting with the garlicky pan juices.\n6. Return the chicken to the pan and let everything rest together for 1–2 minutes.\n7. *(Optional)* Finish with a squeeze of lemon juice and a pat of butter for a light pan sauce.\n8. Garnish with fresh parsley and serve immediately.\n\n> \uD83D\uDCA1 **Chef's Tip:** Cook the chicken first so its juices flavor the pan — your fish will thank you!"}]},"meta":{"provider":"claude","tokensUsed":452,"ingredientsCount":3,"fallbackUsed":false,"originalProvider":"","timestamp":"2026-03-18T15:08:19.4399317Z"},"error":null}
