2026-03-18 15:08:39.137 +00:00 [INF] API | POST /api/ai | 200 | 6685ms | Headers: {"Content-Type":"application/json; charset=utf-8"} | Body: {"success":true,"data":{"answers":[{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","text":"# Garlic Chicken & Fish Skillet\n\nA simple one-pan dish where garlic brings everything together!\n\n### Ingredients\n\n**Core:**\n- 2 chicken thighs (boneless)\n- 2 fish fillets (tilapia, cod, or similar)\n- 4–5 garlic cloves, minced\n\n**Optional:**\n- Olive oil or butter\n- Salt & pepper\n- Fresh lemon juice\n- Fresh herbs (parsley or thyme)\n- Chili flakes\n\n---\n\n### Instructions\n\n1. **Season** the chicken and fish with salt, pepper, and half the minced garlic. Let sit for 10 minutes.\n2. **Heat** a skillet over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil or butter *(optional but recommended)*.\n3. **Sear the chicken** for 5–6 minutes per side until golden and cooked through. Remove and set aside.\n4. **Lower the heat** to medium and add the remaining garlic to the same pan, stirring for 30 seconds until fragrant.\n5. **Cook the fish** fillets for 2–3 minutes per side, basting with the garlicky pan juices.\n6. **Return the chicken** to the pan and let everything rest together for 1–2 minutes.\n7. **Finish** with a squeeze of lemon juice and fresh herbs *(optional)* and serve immediately.\n\n> \uD83D\uDC68‍\uD83C\uDF73 **Chef's Tip:** Add the fish last — it cooks much faster than chicken and stays tender that way!"}]},"meta":{"provider":"claude","tokensUsed":449,"ingredientsCount":3,"fallbackUsed":false,"originalProvider":"","timestamp":"2026-03-18T15:08:39.1368064Z"},"error":null}
